Recommendations
We recommended, and the Municipal Accountant agreed to:
Ensure compliance with IPSAS 1 and IPSAS 20 by providing the required disclosures in the Notes to FS, specifically on the aggregate remuneration of management personnel who are retiring in the next reporting period, as well as the Municipality’s adoption of IPSAS 39 in accordance with COA Circular No. 2024-009;
Provide disclosure in the Notes to FS on the nature of the leave benefits payable and their expected payment for at least the following year;
Properly disclose the implementation of the above-mentioned resolution along with EO 138, their details, and financial and non-financial effects on the LGU;
Revise the account name of the account “Share from Internal Revenue Allotment” to “Share from National Tax Allotment” in compliance with the above-mentioned resolution and EO; and
Moving forward, to study constantly the International Federation of Accountants (IFAC) publications, COA accounting rules and regulations, and consult with the audit team.

We reiterated our recommendation and Management agreed to comply with the regulations on settlement of accounts by 
a) regularly monitor the status of NSs and NDs; 
b) enforce the submission of required documents in the NS; 
c) enforce settlement of the NDs without delay or requiring the Municipal Treasurer to deduct from the salary of the persons liable in the Notice of Disallowance; and 
d) draw up adjusting entries to correct the balance of the 1-03-06-010, Receivables – Disallowances/Changes account and submit the required documents for settlements for the issuance of NSSDC.

The Management to comply with the regulations on settlement of accounts by: 
a) monitoring regularly the status of NSs and NDs; 
b) enforcing the submission of required documents in the NS; and 
c) enforcing settlement of the NDs without delay or requiring the Municipal Treasurer to deduct from the salary of the persons liable in the Notice of Disallowance; 
d) draw up adjusting entries to correct the balance of the 1-03-06-010, Receivables – Disallowances/Changes account and submit the required documents for settlements for the issuance of NSSDC.

We recommended that the management will direct the;
a.	Municipal Accountant to prepare the proper lapsing schedule and present the Property, Plant and Equipment with the corresponding depreciation and impairment schedule in the Notes as prescribed. (Please refer to GAM-LGU volume I, annex 10 for guidance)

b.	Municipal Treasurer/Inventory Committee to conduct thorough physical inventory count, provide and put inventory stickers with specification on all PPE for proper identification, to take note all unserviceable asset for possible write-down or disposal and reconcile the actual inventory reports with the records in the accounting office. Furthermore, to maintain property cards or ARE for control and verification. For systematic procedure, strategized the inventory taking and preparation of property cards be done by property classification and/or by location for property located outside the Municipality’s premises.

The management direct the; 

a.	The Municipal Treasurer or the inventory custodian to prepare the RIS with the end user’s request and submit the Summary of Supply and Material Issued (SSMI), for validation and verification and for all future transactions, for internal control and traceability purposes;

b.	In-charged for the distribution to prepare the corresponding list of beneficiaries or recipients with proof of acknowledgement or signature as evidence of the distribution, consumption and/or expenses; and

c.	Municipal Accountant to adjust the remaining balance not yet consumed or issued if any, and furnished this office the corresponding RIS. And prospectively, record all procured goods and supplies using asset method and recognized expenses only upon receipts of the RIS copy.

The Management to direct the Accounting Office to properly recognize and present in the financial statements the cost and the respective accumulated depreciation of each component of the Local Road Networks, in compliance with Item IV-Accounting Policies of COA Circular No. 2015-008.

The Municipal Mayor, as provided by COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015, require the coordination and cooperation of the following personnel:

a.   Local Accountant-
1.	Prepare the Journal Voucher to record the beginning balance of the road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Networks Ledger Card (Annex D), respectively;

2.	Support the JEV with the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, working paper on the distribution of costs for the road components, and working paper on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost for road components with no available cost per registry;

3.	Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and components for every road network; 

4.	Prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year;

5.	Disclose the total road network of the Municipality in the Notes to the Financial Statements of the Agency (Annex B).

b. Municipal Treasurer/ General Services Officer
6.	Maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map; 

7.	Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components (Annex E).

8.	Render a Report on Local Road Network of the Municipality (Annex A).

c. Municipal Engineer 
9.	Provide the local accountant and the general services officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

d.  Inventory Committee 
10. Prepare the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System of the Municipality (Annex C), in accordance with this circular.

The Management to comply with the regulations on settlement of accounts by: 

a) monitoring regularly the status of NSs and NDs; 
b) enforcing the submission of required documents in the NS; and 
c) enforcing settlement of the NDs without delay or requiring the Municipal Treasurer to deduct from the salary of the persons liable in the Notice of Disallowance; 
d) draw up adjusting entries to correct the balance of the 1-03-06-010, Receivables – Disallowances/Changes account and submit the required documents for settlements for the issuance of NSSDC.

